Clytia hemisphaerica
has recently become a model organism for the study of various biological processes (
Cook et al . 2016
). Even a draft genome of the species has been assembled (
Leclere et al . 2019
), with distinct transcriptome signatures in polyp, medusa, and planula larva stages.

